OL,3,CJersey bus company 'seriously
OL,4,Cconsiders' ending cash payments
OL,6,FThe head of Jersey's bus service says
OL,7,Fthey would "seriously consider"
OL,8,Fremoving cash payments from their
OL,9,Fservice.
OL,11,FKevin Hart told a scrutiny panel that
OL,12,Fthe bus service would save #65,000 a
OL,13,Fyear if they went cashless.
OL,15,FCurrently, the bus service must take
OL,16,Fcash payments due to contractual
OL,17,Fobligations set by Jersey's government.
